                        <h1>October 8, 2008</h1>
                                                               
                        

<H4>October 8, 2008</H4><BR>
<H3>Check Out Our Blog - Digital Dialogue </H3>
<P>Want to be the first to know about the latest news for the 2009 International CES and the CE industry as a whole? <A href="http://blog.ce.org/" target=_blank>Visit our blog!</A>&nbsp; <A href="http://blog.ce.org/" target=_blank>Digital Dialogue</A> covers everything related to the CE industry, the latest CEA happenings and, of course, everything you need to know about the International CES. Updated weekly, you will find the latest on registration, events, keynotes, industry insiders, awards, transportation and much more. We love comments – so please make sure to drop us a line.</P>
<H3>Pre-Registered Media List coming soon </H3>
<P>Don’t wait until you’re at the show to get in front of the media – share your exciting news before it starts! The pre-registered list will be available on CESweb.org beginning November 5, 2008 and will be updated weekly - all you need is your CES Exhibitor ID number. For questions, contact Allison Carney at acarney@CE.org or (703) 907-7603. </P>
<H3>CNET Best of CES Awards</H3>
<P><STRONG>Finalists announced: 10 a.m. Friday, January 9<BR>Award show: 2 p.m. Saturday, January 10<BR>LVCC, South Hall 3 Lobby, CNET Live Stage<BR></STRONG>Each year, CNET editors receive hundreds of entries from companies hoping to have their products selected as one of the hottest at the show.</P>
<P>The winners of the Best of CES awards are selected by CNET editors, who are looking for the most innovative product that will set the standard from which all other products are measured in the coming year.&nbsp; Submission is free and can be <A href="http://www.cnet.com/best-of-ces/" target=_blank>accessed through an online form.</A>&nbsp; The deadline to submit is December 8, 2008.&nbsp; Awards are given in 10 categories, including Best of Show and the People's Voice, which is chosen by CNET's online audience.</P>
<H3>Send Us Your Product Images </H3>
<P>In preparation for the 2009 International CES, the CEA Communications Department is soliciting press contact details and high-resolution images of your products to include in our <A href="http://www.cnet.com/best-of-ces/" target=_blank>division press kits that are hosted online</A>. This is a fantastic opportunity for you to spotlight your company's hottest new products and leverage the excitement surrounding CES for additional press coverage.</P>
<P>All you need to do is send an e-mail to skidera@CE.org with the subject line of "CES Hi-Res Product Images," by December 15.&nbsp; </P>
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text>Include in the body of the e-mail your product division and a press contact person for your company with full name, title, company name, address, phone, fax, email and URL. </LI>
<LI class=text>Attach up to three (3) product shots as high-resolution images (300 dpi or higher in jpeg or any other image format). </LI>
<LI class=text>For each product image sent, include one sentence with product name, model number and MSRP. </LI>
<LI class=text>Take advantage of this opportunity to reach hundreds of members of the press!</LI></UL><BR>
