<H3>Capture the CES Executive Channel with CE Vision Magazine </H3>
<P>As the producer of the International CES, the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) draws the core of the CES audiencefor its Consumer Electronics Vision magazine readership. Companies advertised and mentioned within CE Vision get exposure with the CES elite. </P>
<P>This award-winning publication goes to the top 23,000 CE executives worldwide. The magazine also has exclusive distribution at the shuttles at Reagan National, LaGuardia and Logan airports.</P>
<P>Capture the attention of attendees and executives before they hit the show floor. Four key reasons to place your company in CE Vision's November/December issue: </P>
<OL type=1>
<LI class=text>Drive Booth Attendance: As the official magazine of CEA, CE Vision gives readers inside access on what to see during the show. This issue includes a supplement on exhibitors at CES Unveiled@NY, the show's annual press preview, looks at the hottest growth areas and what exhibitors in the CES TechZones plan to highlight. </LI>
<LI class=text>Strengthen your Corporate Brand: More than 13,800 company presidents, owners and CEOs look to CE Vision for the latest on industry research, forecasts and trends to stay informed. CE Vision provides you with a positive space to develop your corporate leadership image in the global CE business community. </LI>
<LI class=text>Go Global: As the only CE trade publication with international coverage, this issue examines how environmental issues could impact your businesses and what you need to know. </LI>
<LI class=text>Position your Brand on Critical Issues: CE Vision also looks at next-gen video technology coming after the digital transition is complete, 3-G technology, why XGP may be a game changer and how retailers can increase profits with warranties and accessories. </LI></OL>
<P>What’s more, the January/February show issue has bonus distribution of 28,000 copies at CES with premiere placements throughout the show, including VIP lounges, press rooms, CEA member lounges and at the Innovations Showcase. It also is distributed at the 2009 CEA Winter Retreat, Digital Music Forum East and Greener Gadgets Conference. The March/April issue has bonus distribution at the CEA Washington Forum in Washington, D.C. </P>
<P><STRONG>Advertise Today</STRONG><BR>Contact Jason Stookey at 703-907-7678, <A href="mailto:jstookey@CE.org">jstookey@CE.org</A> for advertising opportunities. Space closes October 13. Materials are due October 20. </P>
